```

### New reducer cases:
- `ADD_LIGHT` — append to `lightPlacements` (same pattern as `ADD_MANNEQUIN`, line 198)
- `UPDATE_LIGHT` — map + match by `id + shotId`, spread partial updates
- `REMOVE_LIGHT` — filter by `id + shotId`
- `SET_SCENE_LIGHTING` — merge partial into `sceneLighting`
- `SET_LIGHTING_MODE` — set boolean

### Modify existing cases:

**`SET_ACTIVE_SHOT` (line 180)** — Add copy-on-switch logic:
```typescript
case 'SET_ACTIVE_SHOT': {
  const prevShot = state.shots[state.activeShotIndex];
  const nextShot = state.shots[action.index];
  let newLights = state.lightPlacements;

  if (prevShot && nextShot && prevShot.id !== nextShot.id) {
    const nextHasLights = state.lightPlacements.some(l => l.shotId === nextShot.id);
    if (!nextHasLights) {
      const cloned = state.lightPlacements
        .filter(l => l.shotId === prevShot.id)
        .map(l => ({ ...l, id: crypto.randomUUID(), shotId: nextShot.id }));
      newLights = [...state.lightPlacements, ...cloned];
    }
  }
  return { ...state, activeShotIndex: action.index, lightPlacements: newLights };
}
```

**`REMOVE_SHOT` (line 149)** — Also filter out `lightPlacements` for removed shot.

**`RESET` (line 316)** — Already returns `initialState` which will include new defaults.

